Mail header sample
Conclusion and recommendations

Here's the additional content to include in your PDF report:
Additional Section: Phishing Email Sample & Header Analysis

1. Sample Phishing Email

sql
Copy
Edit
From: "Apple Support" <no-reply@apple-secure-login.com>  
To: user@example.com  
Subject: Your Apple ID is Locked – Verify Now

Dear Customer,

We detected suspicious activity in your Apple account. To protect your information, we have temporarily locked your Apple ID.
To restore access, please verify your account using the link below:
https://apple-id-confirmation.com/secure
If we don’t hear from you within 24 hours, your account will be permanently disabled.

Thank you,  
Apple Security Team

2. Sender Email Address Analysis

Field	Value	Observation
From	no-reply@apple-secure-login.com	Spoofed domain mimicking Apple
Display Name	Apple Support	Legit-sounding, easily faked
Reply-To	Not shown, often differs	Used to misdirect replies to attacker-controlled email

Conclusion: The sender address uses domain spoofing to mislead the recipient.

3. Email Header Sample

Paste this into https://mailheader.org:
vbnet
Copy
Edit
Return-Path: <no-reply@apple-secure-login.com>
Received: from mail.fakehost.net (mail.fakehost.net [203.0.113.45])
    by inbound.example.com with ESMTP id ABC123XYZ;
    Wed, 6 Aug 2025 10:00:45 +0530
Received-SPF: fail (example.com: domain of apple-secure-login.com does not designate 203.0.113.45 as permitted sender)
From: "Apple Support" <no-reply@apple-secure-login.com>
To: user@example.com
Subject: Your Apple ID is Locked – Verify Now
Message-ID: <apple-id123@fakehost.net>
Date: Wed, 6 Aug 2025 10:00:43 +0530
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/html

4. Header Discrepancy Analysis

Field	Discrepancy
SPF Check	FAIL – IP not authorized to send from that domain
Return-Path	Non-Apple domain used (apple-secure-login.com)
Message-ID	Not from Apple servers (fakehost.net)
Mail Server IP	Unfamiliar server (203.0.113.45)

5. Final Conclusion

This email is a clear phishing attempt, using:
Spoofed sender domain
Fake urgency
Invalid SPF (as shown in header)
Misleading display name

Recommended Actions

Do not interact with links or reply
Report to IT/security team
Use header analysis tools to verify legitimacy
Implement DMARC/SPF/DKIM policies organization-wide
